RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLONDE DYNAMO had a good position in the second flight tracking outside, took closer order to the front pair at the five sixteenths marker, was roused for more five wide at the furlong pole and wore down the leaders in deep stretch to just get up for the win. MY ASSISTANT prompted outside in the beginning, was content to sit just off the leader on the turn, contested for the front four wide straightening out for the drive and fought on stubbornly with runners on either side to the wire just missing in a gutsy effort. ROSES ARE FREE pulled the rider to the lead down the back straight, set the pace up front having a narrow advantage on the turn, was headed outside at the top of the lane, battled until the last eighth and gave way grudgingly in deep stretch inside at the wire. HARD ROCK WARRIOR broke out to begin, trailed the field down the backstretch as well as on the turn, swung out widest in the seven path for the drive, was full of run in the final furlong and closed in well to capture a minor share at the wire. DROWNINGNCHOCOLATE settled in mid field four deep down the backside, kept pace with the leaders outside rivals on the turn, shifted out six wide for the stretch drive and was one paced in the last fulrong. KIMONO KATE was nestled behind the top pair in the beginning on the rail, was nudged on to go after the engaging leaders with five sixteenths to run, offered little response and faded between horses in the final eighth of a mile. DOO DAH travelled on the rail in mid pack down the backside, made little headway on the fence through the turn and had nothing to give inside for the stretch drive. SHEZ A SEALY stalked on the inside near the back of the pack in the early going, save ground running on the fence throughout the turn but could not get involved between runners in the four path running to the finish. BLUEBERRY DOLL was brushed inside at the start, settled near the rear outside down the back straight, made little impression on the turn and had nothing to give in the stretch drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MACHINA travelled in the middle of the field four deep down the backside, was coaxed at the three furlong pole, began to reel in the leaders just outside, loomed the threat four wide at the top of the lane, collared the frontrunner at the sixteenth pole and was edging away nearing the wire. SMART BIRD took command from the start, was pressured inside on the turn, put away the early pace foe at the top of the stretch, was collared outside by the winner at the eighth pole, could not hold hold off the late surge and settled for second best on this day in a gritty effort. CHROME'S ANGEL stalked near the rear three deep down the backstretch, followed the path behind the winner on the turn, was checked mildly in upper stretch, angled out to the five path for the drive and regrouped to finish up gamely to close in and capture third at the the wire. ALBERTA BE MINE was squeezed at the start, tracked three deep outside in the early going, was roused midpoint on the turn to get involved up front at the top of the lane, could not find more late between foes in the stretch to threaten and settled on a small share in the end. GOLD FORESTER tracked two deep between rivals in the beginning, was taken back off the pace at the half, kept in touch with the leaders on the turn to be in with a chance straightening out for the drive but could not be a menace in the late stages of the race. JOLENE JOLENE broke out to begin, pressed inside down the back straight, hounded the pacesetter on the rail throughout the turn and could not find another gear and finished evenly on the fence to the wire. SOCIAL DRINKER was pushed in at the break, trailing down the backside, began to smartly pick up rivals outside commencing at the three furlong marker, continued to rally outside to be in the mix of things widest in the seven path in upper stretch but could not sustain the run and stalled in the final eighth. FOREST MAIDEN broke in at the start, settled between foes in mid field at the half mile marker, was urged for more outside three furlongs from the wire making little impact and could not be a factor running through the stretch. ITS A BIRDIE broke inwards to begin, travelled on the fence in the middle of the pack at the half, was ridden along on the rail with three eighths to go losing ground to runners on the turn and was empty for the stretch run.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HELL BENT was unhurried to trail the field down the back straight on the outside, still could see the field running on the turn, was behind a wall of rivals at the top of the stretch, began to weave through traffic in mid stretch, found clear running room finally at the sixteenth pole and surged late to just get up at the wire in a well timed stretch rally. SMALL TALK was outside stalking in the third flight down the backstretch, started to gain momentum outside runners three furlongs from the finish, angled to the six path looking the main threat turning for home, took command at the furlong marker and was just caught at the wire by the surging winner. SPANISH PRINCE had a loose lead down the backstretch, continued to dictate the pace on the turn, was headed outside at the top of the lane, put away that challenger in upper stretch, could not hold off the late closers in the last sixteenth and held on for the show at the finish. TOURIST'S DREAM chased on the rail at the three quarter pole, was shuffled on the fence entering the turn, offered a mild run two wide outside to be in range four wide at the quarter pole and was gaining mildly down the lane to be involved for the show award at the finish. PRINCE OF THIEVES was bumped inside at the start, stalked at the back down the backstretch, was in hand on the rail through the first part of the turn, shifted out with five sixteenths to go, angled out widest in the seven path for the drive and showed good energy passing some in the late stages of the race. NEWPORT AGENT was bumped between foes to start, settled near the rear two deep down the backside, offered a mild run at the half to the quarter marker and faded between at the eighth pole. JMR PURE SENSATION broke out bumping outside foe to begin, travelled near the back of the pack on the rail, could not get into contention inside on the turn and was not a presence in the stretch drive. ORPHAN HALLIE stalked in the third flight on the rail down the backstretch, could not quicken with others three eighths from home and flattened in the three path running through the stretch. EXULT was three deep outside horses tracking the pacesetter, took closer order chasing the frontrunner just outside on the turn, loomed four wide at the top of the lane and backed away between runners at the furlong marker. CANYOUHEARMENOW tracked with runners on either side in the beginning, was roused with three furlongs remaining, could not keep up to the leaders on the turn and retreated on the fence through the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEGUIMI was urged from the start, quickly moved clear and shifted in to dictate the pace inside, was never thoroughly challenged saving ground and setting the tempo, put to urging at the top of the stretch and had enough in reserve to hold sway while being kept to the task. MALIBU UPROAR exchanged a light bump at the start, was coaxed forward from between runners early, moved nearer the rail tracking off the pace inside saving ground, advanced inside a rival on the far turn, came out a bit with aim on the winner, could make no headway despite all-out urging. STOP THE HUMBUG settled off the pace inside early, was off the rail heading to the far turn and beginning to advance, moved out from three to four wide late on that bend gaining between rivals to the top of the stretch where five wide, was best of the rest but no match for the top pair. MAYITO was off the early leaders but within range two to three wide early, pushed along leaving the backstretch, fanned six wide into upper stretch between runners, ran on but needed more. EXECUTIVE GIANT was just a bit fractious in the gate, in just a bit tight early, shifted in on the first turn, continued to save ground on the far turn while making up distance on the main group, improved inside late. DE ONLY SOLUTION exchanged a light bump at the start, was well-placed tracking inside up close, saved ground through both turns advancing inside a tiring rival at the quarter pole then shifted out coming three to four wide into upper stretch and with momentum but could not sustain the run and flattened out. JACK THE CAT settled in the back half of the field off the fence in the two to three path, swung five to six wide turning for home, ran on evenly while never menacing. HIT THE POINT lacked early speed and was unhurried at the rear far off the pace, passed tired foes in the stretch. WENJACK shifted in racing mid-pack outside foes three to four wide into the first turn, was still in position and urged along coming past the quarter pole but floated wide at that juncture coming into upper stretch seven deep, faltered and faded. FIRST SPRING raced outside off the pace mostly three to five wide and was never near enough to threaten. SOCIETY JOE moved forward after the break under some encouragement from the rider, stalked the eventual winner about a length and a half off that one racing three deep, came up empty.

ANTIGONE was last outside down the back straight, offered a mild turn of foot four wide at the three furlong marker, swung out widest in the eight path at the top of the stretch but could not get involved running to the wire. RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 9 7 1/2F Inner turf CR: 67. Claiming Purse 29000. INNER TURF FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLIFF'S HEAD settled comfortably on the fence in midfield at the half, rallied inside on the far turn gaining on the leaders, angled three wide for the drive and accelerated at the furlong pole to draw away at the finish. GRANDE BELLA tracked on the outside getting a good position two wide into the first turn, prompted the pace down the backstretch, bid for the lead midway on the final turn, poked her head in front briefly in upper stretch but was not match for the winner late while comfortably besting the rest for second money. ZIPPITY DAY stalked near the rear four wide on the first turn, travelled four deep in midpack down the backside, was scrubbed on for more with three eighths to go, rallied between runners in the final furlong and got up for a small share in the end. MERITAMEN hopped at the break seeing the field in the first turn, was headstrong fighting the rider down the backstretch for wide outside horses, was picking up rivals through the far turn, was on hold briefly behind tiring runners midway on the far turn and offered a good finish four wide to be involved for the minors at the finish. LADY IN RED was hustled to get the lead entering the first turn, continued to set the fractions having a slim advantage down the back straight, was urged to keep the lead midway on the far turn, was collared in upper stretch and faded on the rail in the last sixteenth. SMARTY ILLUSION was void of speed inside trailing into the first turn, advanced some on the fence down the backside and showed late energy through the stretch to pass weary rivals to the wire. WAR'S END KISS was nestled behind the leader into the first turn, had a good spot watching the top two at the half, was urged for more trying to keep up with the leaders at the three eighths pole, was willingly between runners at the top of the lane and weakened in the final sixteenth. MANITOULIN ISLAND was in hand on the rail early in midfield, was nudged on for more with three furlongs to go, could not make up any ground and yielded in the stretch. BITTERSWEETBIZNESS stalked between rivals on the first turn, advanced outside runners down the back straight, was in the mix for a share midpoint on the far turn and gave way with rivals on either side in mid stretch. TENPENNY NAIL trailed the field into the field turn, was last down the backstretch, still could see the field on the final turn and was not involved in the stretch run.
